        <num>CC 234</num>
        <heading>234.  Parental authority; custody award</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 234.  Parental authority; custody award
Parental authority continues during marriage, unless modified by a judgment
awarding custody to one parent, by a joint custody implementation order, or by a judgment
awarding custody to a person other than a parent.
An ascendant, other than a parent, who is awarded custody has parental authority. 
The authority of a person who is awarded custody, other than a parent or an ascendant, is
governed by the rules of tutorship, unless modified by court order.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
